## Full Agent Catalog

### Architecture Team
- **architect** (opus): System architecture designer. Designs scalable, maintainable architectures with clear component boundaries and data flow.
- **ha-specialist** (sonnet): High-availability specialist. Designs fault-tolerant systems with redundancy, failover, and disaster recovery.
- **devops** (sonnet): DevOps engineer. Handles CI/CD pipelines, Docker, Kubernetes, infrastructure as code, and deployment automation.

### Backend Team
- **api-architect** (opus): API designer and backend architect. Creates RESTful/GraphQL APIs with proper validation, error handling, and documentation.
- **perf-engineer** (sonnet): Performance engineer. Profiles, benchmarks, and optimizes code for speed, memory, and throughput.
- **exchange-specialist** (sonnet): Exchange/trading domain specialist. Expert in exchange APIs, order management, WebSocket feeds, and market data.

### Frontend Team
- **ux-designer** (opus): UX/UI designer. Creates intuitive interfaces, component hierarchies, and user interaction flows.
- **react-dev** (sonnet): React/Next.js developer. Implements components, hooks, state management, and frontend build pipelines.
- **dashboard-specialist** (sonnet): Dashboard and data visualization specialist. Creates charts, real-time displays, and monitoring interfaces.

### Integration Team
- **saas** (sonnet): SaaS integration architect. Designs multi-tenant systems, subscription billing, onboarding flows, and API rate limiting.
- **security** (opus): Security engineer. Audits for vulnerabilities, implements auth/authz, encryption, and secure coding practices.
- **db-architect** (sonnet): Database architect. Designs schemas, migrations, query optimization, indexing strategies, and data modeling.

### QA Team
- **test-engineer** (sonnet): Test engineer. Writes unit, integration, and e2e tests with comprehensive coverage strategies.
- **qa-tester** (haiku): QA tester. Executes test suites, reports bugs, validates edge cases, and performs regression testing.
- **verifier** (haiku): Build verifier. Validates that code compiles, tests pass, and builds succeed before integration.

### Optimization Team
- **perf-engineer** (sonnet): Performance engineer (see Backend Team).
- **code-simplifier** (sonnet): Code simplifier. Reduces complexity, eliminates dead code, improves readability without changing behavior.
- **scientist** (opus): Algorithm scientist. Designs optimal algorithms, evaluates time/space complexity, and selects best data structures.

### Bug Team
- **debugger** (opus): Expert debugger. Traces execution paths, inspects state, and isolates root causes with systematic analysis.
- **build-fixer** (sonnet): Build/config fixer. Resolves compilation errors, dependency conflicts, and configuration issues.
- **root-cause-analyst** (opus): Root cause analyst. Performs deep causal analysis of bugs, failures, and system anomalies.

### Planning Team
- **planner** (opus): Project planner. Breaks down complex tasks into phases, creates execution plans, and defines milestones.
- **analyst** (sonnet): Requirements analyst. Analyzes specs, identifies gaps, validates assumptions, and clarifies ambiguous requirements.
- **critic** (opus): Design critic. Challenges assumptions, identifies risks, and provides constructive feedback on proposed designs.

### Review Team
- **code-reviewer** (opus): Senior code reviewer. Evaluates code quality, patterns, naming, SOLID principles, and maintainability.
- **security-reviewer** (opus): Security code reviewer. Identifies injection attacks, auth bypasses, data leaks, and insecure patterns.
- **quality-reviewer** (sonnet): Quality assurance reviewer. Validates test coverage, documentation completeness, and coding standard compliance.

### Specialist Agents
- **doc-writer** (sonnet): Technical writer. Creates API docs, READMEs, architecture docs, and inline code documentation.
- **migrator** (sonnet): Migration specialist. Handles database migrations, API versioning, dependency upgrades, and breaking changes.
- **refactorer** (sonnet): Refactoring specialist. Restructures code for better modularity, reduces coupling, and improves testability.

