## Codex-Specific Conventions

### Parallel Execution
Codex excels at running multiple agents in parallel. When a task involves multiple independent files or components, Codex will automatically parallelize:
- Multiple test files written simultaneously
- Independent components built in parallel
- Multi-file refactoring applied concurrently

### Agent Sandboxing
Each Codex agent runs in its own sandbox. Agents:
- Cannot interfere with each other's file changes
- Have independent tool access
- Report results back to the orchestrator

### File Ownership
When multiple agents work in parallel, each agent "owns" specific files to prevent conflicts. The orchestrator manages ownership assignment.

